					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7844922#post-4018872</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7844922/tension-and-release#post-4018872</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 09 Oct 2018 13:45:42 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Stallmantic</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3472766</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I have&#8230; issues with the concept. This is a well-written article, but the ending is kinda bleh. I feel like I'm being a contrarian in saying that &quot;He understands the concept of horror itself&quot; feels like a cop out, and isn't elaborated on at all. My first reaction was &quot;What?&quot; followed by a quick &quot;How?&quot; and shortly after, a &quot;Why?&quot; Honestly, if you could write a tale elaborating on this concept, what exactly that means, how they stop it, etc, my opinions would probably be reversed but as it is now, its just a confusing tease. It would also disprove my opinion that it's impossible to properly conceptualize &quot;horror itself&quot;, because clearly you would have done it.</p> <p>PM me if you do make a second one but for now I'm resolving to a tentative -1.</p> <p>Good luck with the contest though!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
